net.hudup.core

Class RegisterTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.RegisterTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class RegisterTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cloneable
    Plug-in manager is responsible for discovering and managing registered recommendation algorithms. The class that implements PluginManager is Firer. Alg is the most abstract interface for all algorithms. Every algorithm has a unique name. Every algorithm is registered in system register table and identified by its name. Such system register table is modeled as this RegisterTable class. Actually, plug-in manager discovers automatically all algorithms via their names at the booting time and requires PluginStorage to add such algorithms into register tables represented by RegisterTable classes. After Hudup framework started, it is easy to retrieve any any algorithms by looking up algorithms in register tables from PluginStorage. Please pay attention that system register tables are stored in a so-called plug-in storage which is represented by PluginStorage class.
    RegisterTable provides two important methods as follows:
    • Method register(Alg) registers a given algorithm. This method is called by PluginManager.discover(String) at starting time of Hudup. A algorithm which is registered in RegisterTable will be added in the internal map algMap.
    • Method query(String) retrieves an algorithm by its name with attention that such algorithm is named by returned value of its Alg.getName() method. Method query(String) is often called by evaluator and recommendation service to retrieve specified algorithms. A algorithm which is unregistered in RegisterTable will be removed from the internal map algMap.
    Note, general algorithm is represented by Alg interface. Alg has five typical inherited interfaces as follows:
    • Recommendation algorithm Recommender.
    • Context template schema manager CTSManager.
    • Data set parser DatasetParser.
    • External query ExternalQuery.
    • Metric Metric.
